法規內容.條文內容:
Persons with one of the following qualifications may apply for skills certification of Class B certified technician:
1. Obtaining a Class C technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied and also receiving vocational training of related job category for no less than 800 hours in accumulation, or engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than two years;
2. Obtaining a Class C technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied and also holding a diploma of senior high school or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level, or a senior student currently in the senior high school;
3. Obtaining a Class C technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied and a student currently in the third grade of a five-year junior college, two-year or three-year junior college, technology college, or university.
4. Receiving vocational training of related job category for 400 hours in accumulation and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than three years;
5. Receiving vocational training of related job category for 800 hours in accumulation and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than two years;
6. Receiving vocational training of related job category for no less than 1,600 hours in accumulation;
7. Receiving vocational training of related job category for no less than 800 hours in accumulation and also holding a diploma of senior high school or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level;
8. Receiving vocational training of related job category for 400 hours in accumulation, engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than one year and also holding a diploma of senior high school or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level;
9. Receiving apprentice training of related job category for two years and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than two years;
10. Holding a diploma of senior high school or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than two years;
11. Holding a university or higher degree or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level, or a senior student currently in university;
12.Engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than six years.
The vocational training and apprentice training of related job categories referred to in the preceding paragraph shall be reviewed and determined by the Central Competent Authority, and only the participants of foresaid training provided by vocational training agencies (institutions) or government-commissioned units can be accepted.

Persons with one of the following qualifications may apply for skills certification of Class A certified technician:
1. Obtaining a Class B technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than two years;
2. Obtaining a Class B technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied and also receiving vocational training of related job category for no less than 800 hours in accumulation;
3. Obtaining a Class B technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied, receiving vocational training of related job category for no less than 800 hours in accumulation and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than one year;
4. Obtaining a Class B technician certificate for the job category of skills certification applied, holding a university or technology college degree or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than one year;
5. Holding a junior college degree or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than four years;
6. Holding a technology college or university degree or a certificate equal to that of foresaid school level and also engaging in work related to the job category of skills certification applied for no less than three years.
The vocational training of related job categories referred to in the preceding paragraph shall be reviewed and determined by the Central Competent Authority, and only the participants of foresaid training provided by vocational training agencies (institutions) or government-commissioned units can be accepted.
